asset.hookText:
BTU power is often used as a deciding factor when choosing a grill to buy. This video explains how the BTU number is less important than the maximum temperature a grill can produce. As an example, infrared grills use less BTUs than convective grills and produce the same high heat.

Produced by Char-Broil for Home Depot.

For more information about TRU-Infrared technology visit http://charbroil.com/tru_infrared
